    "extras": [
      "Israel Railways is the smoothest way to move between Tel Aviv, Ben Gurion Airport, Jerusalem and Haifa, but there is no train to Nazareth, the Dead Sea or Eilat.",
      "Egged buses cover the Dead Sea, Masada and Eilat well enough for independent travel, but check Friday/Saturday service carefully because Shabbat schedules are limited.",
      "Sheruts are useful when trains and buses stop for Shabbat, especially on Tel Aviv-Jerusalem runs and some northern routes.",
      "The Western Wall and Yad Vashem are free; Masada, Ein Gedi, the Tel Aviv Museum of Art, Israel Museum and Eilat reef attractions are the main paid anchors in this plan.",
      "Domestic flights between Tel Aviv and Ramon Airport near Eilat save significant time if you do not want a 5- to 7-hour bus leg.",
      "Carry water, sun protection and a swimsuit/shower kit for Dead Sea days because the salt and desert heat are much harsher than the city legs."
    ],
